## Conversation
Spun off from the weave-instrument skill work. Dan asked on Slack (thread p1782508728616839) whether the SDKs print a Weave URL on init, because the skill's "Verify" step told agents to watch for a printed link. Investigation found an asymmetry: Python's weave.init() prints "View Weave data at <url>" but the Node SDK printed only "Initializing project: <entity>/<project>" with no URL. User: "Make a stacked PR where you fix the TS to do what python does, then change this skill back to be more appropriate." This is the bottom PR of that stack; the skill PR (#7370) stacks on top and depends on it.

## Actions
- sdks/node/src/clientApi.ts:140 — changed `console.log(\`Initializing project: ${projectId}\`)` to `console.log(\`View Weave data at https://${domain}/${projectId}/weave\`)`.
- Confirmed Python's format: weave/trace/init_message.py:119 prints `f"View Weave data at {urls.project_weave_root_url(entity_name, project_name)}"` (→ https://wandb.ai/<entity>/<project>/weave) via logger.info, called unconditionally from weave_init.py:278.
- `domain` and `projectId` are both already in scope in init(): destructured from getWandbConfigs() (clientApi.ts:87) and built at :101. No new imports.
- urls.ts: defaultDomain='wandb.ai' (:4); domain = isDefaultBaseUrl ? defaultDomain : resolvedHost (:65). So on the default base URL the Node line is byte-identical to Python's; on a custom host it correctly uses that host.

